==English==
===Noun===
'''za'''

# An old [[solfeggio]] name for [[B flat]]; the seventh [[harmonic]], as heard in the [[aeolian]] [[string]]; so called by Tartini. It was long considered a false, but is the true note of the chord of the [[flat seventh]].

===Etymology 2===
From ''pizza,'' shortened.
